<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://lum.xrgaming.net/ubb/Forum1/HTML/001080.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000080"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#ffffff" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Stan the guard</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">  I've been gettin ruled by gm swords with my gm fencer. I'm saying its pitiful how I'm gettin hammered by the Hally. Anyone else had this problem with thier fencing?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Pander</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">I have a GM swords/tacs, 0 anat, 94 st, 36 dex tank mage.  I got a cutlass of power with a +10 mod.   I dueled someone with 87st, 54 dex, GM fencing/99.8 tacs.  GM Kryss.  I had 32AR, he had 30AR.  I got my ass handed to me.  Just straight melee, attacking.  We both took off our armor, I went up to 39 dex, he went to 62.  I beat him, kinda close.  I used a katana.  I beat him.  We put armor on, he beat me.  I dunno, while it could all be random as usual, It seems like with armor fencing whomps swords, without it's swords.  Or it could all be random.  But I was curious about this myself, cause a dex monkey fighter that loves to spar always beat me when I didn't use magery, and I was in the mood to test.  <BR>I don't think it's anything recent though...<P>------------------<BR>Pander, Annoyer of Seers, Paladin of Jesters</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Elawyn of Yew</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Fencing has been nerfed for a long long time.<P>It used to be that damage wasn't measured until the end of the 'swing cycle', and back then as a fencer I was almost unbeatable in the duels I fought (By doing the 'fencers dance' and stepping back before that halberd could hit me). They changed it so that the damage is dealt at the beginning of the swing nowadays.<P>Last few melee sessions I've fought haven't been conclusive.<P>Fencing is *still* fairly effective in PvM, and with a 50 something parry my main character can manage anything short of an ogre lord/terathan. <P>As far as I can tell, in straight melee against someone with equivalent stats/skills, a katana will win over a kryss most of the time, but the kryss will win over anything else, especially if you can heal.<P>That said, I still prefer fencing, a Gm Kryss, especially one coated with poison, in the hands of a 100 dex GM Fencer is very effective. A long spear is also very effective against heavily armored opponents. A war fork is a little slower, but does appreciable damage (and only takes one hand.)<P>Overall tho, I'd say that swords still has the advantage.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">Stan the guard</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">  It's interesting that you made that armored / unarmored suggestion. My fencer never fights with armor. I take a few potions and a few bandaids and I'll usually beat an armored opponent. It's just that mage tactic of pre-casting and then hitting with the Hally is hard to live through unless I run [trapped puches or magic arrow]. Don't get me wrong I love precasting paralyze myself but it is very unfair that a master swords 25 dex mage can easily dispatch a gm fencer 100 dex. I say they bump up the mana usage on paralyze so that if I can survive 3 precasted hally strikes the mage should be out of mana between that and keepin' hisself healed. </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
